Generate summary of data processing elements to display in the console

Source: R/04-harmo_process_harmonization.R
show_harmo_error.Rd

Reads annotated data processing elements to list processes, errors, and an overview of each rule of harmonization. This summary report can be used to assist the user in the assessment of harmonization, providing insights on the data structure, fields to investigate, coherence across elements or standard evaluation.

show_harmo_error(harmonization_output)

Arguments

harmonization_output

A tibble, identifying of the annotated data processing elements. These elements are the centralised decision making to perform harmonization of each study-specific dataset.

Value

No object returned, the function sends messages in the console, showing errors in the harmonization process

Details

A data processing element must be a list of at least one data frame or data frame extension (e.g. a tibble) named 'dataProcess'. These elements are the centralised decision making to perform harmonization of each study-specific dataset. The tibble must contain certain columns which participate to the process, including the 'rule_category' and 'harmo_rule'. In addition, the data processing element may follow Maelstrom research standards, and its content can be evaluated accordingly, such as naming convention restriction, columns like 'valueType', and 'harmo status details', and/or any harmonization taxonomy provided.

Examples

{

library(madshapR)
library(lubridate)
library(dplyr)

dataset_MELBOURNE_1 <- DEMO_files$dataset_MELBOURNE_1
dataset_MELBOURNE_2 <- DEMO_files$dataset_MELBOURNE_2
study <-
  study_create(list(dataset_MELBOURNE_1, dataset_MELBOURNE_2)) %>%
  lapply(. %>% slice(1:2))

dataschema <-
  list(Variables =
        DEMO_files$`dataschema - final`$Variables[
           c('name','label:en','valueType')])

data_procelem <- DEMO_files$`data_processing_elements - with error`
harmonization_output <- harmo_process(study,dataschema, data_procelem)

show_harmo_error(harmonization_output)
}
